@FullyTested
public abstract class AbstractTuple<TValue>
extends UnmodifiableForwardingList<TValue>
implements Tuple<TValue>

Abstract super class for tuples. This class can be used to easily create multi-element keys and values for collections. This class also extends UnmodifiableForwardingList so it can conveniently be used as a List when necessary.

For example, if a map needs to be keyed by two elements:

  • You can avoid a map or maps, e.g., Map&lt;?, Map&lt;?, ?>>.
  • You can use a two-element keys, e.g., Map&lt;? extends AbstractTuple&lt;?>, ?>.

Methods ForwardingList.hashCode() and ForwardingList.equals(Object) have correct overrides in this class, making it safe for use in standard Java collections.

Author:
Kevin Connor ARPE (kevinarpe@gmail.com)
See Also:
UnmodifiableForwardingList, Tuple
